{"type":"system","subtype":"thinking_tokens","estimated_tokens":1190,"estimated_tokens_delta":797,"uuid":"9e32d379-75d0-47c7-a3f4-9cd772750d34","session_id":"8652b094-69f7-4255-a583-e0e4cd3fef5d"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HBKcQmUC5G9zvwYBm1gTCN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cluster is responding but there's a `master_not_discovered_exception`. This means:\n1. Authentication is working (password is correct)\n2. The cluster doesn't have a master yet - it needs all 3 nodes to form a cluster since `cluster.initial_master_nodes` is set to all 3\n\nBut wait - the StatefulSet rolls out one pod at a time. The first pod can't become Ready (because the readiness probe requires a healthy cluster with a master), and since it can't become Ready, the StatefulSet won't proceed to deploy the second pod!\nThis is a classic chicken-and-egg problem. The readiness probe is checking for cluster health when I really just need to verify that Elasticsearch is responding, even if it's not fully healthy yet. I should adjust the probe to check for basic connectivity rather than requiring a green or yellow cluster status. Actually, the real goal here is just to verify that Elasticsearch is responding to HTTP requests, regardless of cluster state. I could use a simple curl check against the root endpoint that accepts any valid response, even error codes like 503, as long as the service is actually running and listening. The simplest approach is to make the readiness probe accept any HTTP response from Elasticsearch, since even a 503 or 401 means the process is running. I can use a TCP socket probe on port 9200 instead, which just checks connectivity without worrying about specific status codes. This lets all three pods start up, and once they're all running, the cluster will elect a master and stabilize.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":524,"cache_read_input_tokens":41407,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":524},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8652b094-69f7-4255-a583-e0e4cd3fef5d","uuid":"77c79cb3-7e11-401f-95aa-0b52f12aa4aa","request_id":"req_011CcMyFTgosWd1e2q3BYsZm"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HBKcQmUC5G9zvwYBm1gTCN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The issue is a chicken-and-egg: pod 0's readiness probe requires a cluster master, but the master can't form until the StatefulSet deploys all 3 pods — which it won't do until pod 0 is Ready. I need to relax the readiness probe to just check if ES is listening, not if the cluster is healthy."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":524,"cache_read_input_tokens":41407,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":524},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8652b094-69f7-4255-a583-e0e4cd3fef5d","uuid":"4cc66cee-15c8-4c99-b9c5-50e163994aac","request_id":"req_011CcMyFTgosWd1e2q3BYsZm"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HBKcQmUC5G9zvwYBm1gTCN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011kyGgQBdstLrzyWgfC3uSX","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl patch statefulset elasticsearch -n elasticsearch --type=json -p='[\n  {\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/readinessProbe\",\"value\":{\n    \"exec\":{\n      \"command\":[\"sh\",\"-c\",\"curl -sk -o /dev/null -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\" https://localhost:9200/ | grep -qE \\\"^[0-9]{3}$\\\"\"]\n    },\n    \"initialDelaySeconds\":20,\n    \"periodSeconds\":5,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\":5,\n    \"failureThreshold\":12\n  }},\n  {\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/livenessProbe\",\"value\":{\n    \"tcpSocket\":{\"port\":9300},\n    \"initialDelaySeconds\":60,\n    \"periodSeconds\":30,\n    \"failureThreshold\":5\n  }}\n]' 2>&1","description":"Patch readiness probe to TCP/HTTP check instead of cluster-health"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":524,"cache_read_input_tokens":41407,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":524},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8652b094-69f7-4255-a583-e0e4cd3fef5d","uuid":"7ad58bb7-adcc-4d82-afec-c92547391b89","request_id":"req_011CcMyFTgosWd1e2q3BYsZm"}
